# Normalize line endings: keep text files as LF in the repo regardless of
# the contributor's platform. Prevents phantom whole-file conflicts when
# Windows or Replit checkouts re-introduce CRLF.
* text=auto eol=lf

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Auto-generated files — DO NOT line-merge.
#
# Git's default three-way merge on these produces either garbled output
# (lockfiles) or syntactically-broken JSON (the drizzle journal). Marking
# them `-diff merge=binary` makes Git treat each side as opaque, so a
# conflict surfaces as a single "pick one side" decision instead of
# hundreds of inline `<<<<<<<` hunks scattered through generated text.
#
# Recovery recipe when one of these conflicts (also documented in CLAUDE.md):
#
#   # take whichever side is closer to what you want, then regenerate:
#   git checkout --ours pnpm-lock.yaml      # or --theirs
#   pnpm install                            # regenerates pnpm-lock.yaml
#   git add pnpm-lock.yaml
#
# For the drizzle journal, manually splice the new entries from the other
# side (each entry is keyed by `idx` and `tag`); both branches' new
# migrations must end up in the final `entries` array.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

pnpm-lock.yaml                                  -diff merge=binary
lib/resupply-db/drizzle/meta/_journal.json      -diff merge=binary

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Binary assets — never diff, never line-merge.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

*.png       binary
*.jpg       binary
*.jpeg      binary
*.gif       binary
*.ico       binary
*.webp      binary
*.pdf       binary
*.woff      binary
*.woff2     binary
*.ttf       binary
*.otf       binary
*.eot       binary
*.mp4       binary
*.webm      binary
*.mov       binary
*.zip       binary
*.gz        binary
*.tgz       binary
